/*What are the different types of joins? Please explain how they differ and why certain types
are better in certain situations. */

there are 2 main types of joins: inner joins and outer joins.

Inner joins will only include the rows from each table where they satisfy the join condition 
There are 3 types of outer joins

	Left Join will include all of the rows from the left table and if there is a matching record from the right table, that record will be appended
	to its matching record in the left table. Else a record filled with nulls will 

	Right Join is basically the same as above but different positions

	Full Outer Join will include all records from both the left and the right table. If no matching record was found, then the corresponding
	result fields will have a null value 

